label: Observation type

At the 30 day follow-up observation, a few anthropometry variables were recollected for cases.; Children enrolled in the VIDA study were seen at an enrollment visit and at a 60 day follow-up visit. label: Household wealth index, numerical
definition: Household wealth index from principal component analysis. Positive responses for each of these variables got a score of 1 while negative responses got a score of 0. Used as a component in calculating the WAMI index and ranged from 0 (low) to 8 (high). label: CD36 genotype
definition: Allelic information on the CD36 gene (Cluster of Differentiation 36; Canton et al., 2013), which encodes an integral membrane protein in many cell types. This member of the scavenger receptor family imports fatty acids into cells, and is also an endothelial receptor bound by erythrocytes infected with the malaria parasite Plasmodium falciparum.

label: Total days in all diarrheal episodes; Total diarrheal days
definition: Total number of days that fall within any diarrheal episode since beginning of follow-up. Diarrhea episodes were separated by two diarrhea-free days. Days when data were missing were classified as diarrhea-free (if there were two missing days before a day with diarrhea, the episode started on day with diarrhea). Days with Lactulose:Mannitol (L:M)-induced diarrhea were classified as diarrhea-free. Surveillance was conducted twice weekly for up to 3 years of age to assess illness on all days since the last surveillance visit.

label: Anthropometry assessed in target window
definition: Whether anthropometry was assessed within a +/- 2 day target window or within a 7 day extended window. Anthropometry was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 36m of age, and subsequently every 3 months up to and including 60m of age.

label: Diarrheal episode status
definition: Whether this day of observation marked the beginning of a diarrheal episode or was within a diarrheal episode. Diarrhea episodes were separated by two diarrhea-free days. Days when data are missing were classified as diarrhea-free (if there were two missing days before a day with diarrhea, the episode started on day with diarrhea). Days with Lactulose:Mannitol (L:M)-induced diarrhea were classified as diarrhea-free. Surveillance was conducted twice weekly for up to 3 years of age to assess illness on all days since the last surveillance visit.

label: Diarrheal episode #
definition: All days of observation that fall within a diarrheal episode were coded with the cumulative diarrheal episode count. Diarrhea episodes were separated by two diarrhea-free days. Days with missing data were classified as diarrhea-free (if there were two missing days before a day with diarrhea, the episode started on day with diarrhea). Days with Lactulose:Mannitol (L:M)-induced diarrhea were classified as diarrhea-free. Surveillance was conducted twice weekly for up to 3 years of age to assess illness on all days since the last surveillance visit.; Assessed for each diarrheal episode.

definition: Whether this is the first day of a diarrheal episode. Diarrhea episodes were separated by two diarrhea-free days. Days with Lactulose:Mannitol (L:M)-induced diarrhea were classified as diarrhea-free. Surveillance was conducted twice weekly for up to 3 years of age to assess illness on all days since the last surveillance visit.

label: Day in diarrheal episode
definition: Whether this day of observation falls within a diarrheal episode. Diarrhea episodes were separated by two diarrhea-free days. Days when data were missing were classified as diarrhea-free (if there were two missing days before a day with diarrhea, the episode started on day with diarrhea). Days with Lactulose:Mannitol (L:M)-induced diarrhea were classified as diarrhea-free. label: Cumulative days in this diarrheal episode; Day of diarrheal episode (ex LM induced)
definition: Cumulative count of days that fell within the current diarrheal episode. Diarrhea episodes were separated by two diarrhea-free days. Days with missing data were classified as diarrhea-free (if there were two missing days before a day with diarrhea, the episode started on day with diarrhea). Days with Lactulose:Mannitol (L:M)-induced diarrhea were classified as diarrhea-free. Surveillance was conducted twice weekly for up to 3 years of age to assess illness on all days since the last surveillance visit.

label: Total days in all diarrheal episodes, ex 1st days; Total diarrheal days, ex 1st day
definition: Total number of days that fall within any diarrheal episode during follow-up, excluding the first day of each diarrheal episode. To calculate the time at risk for a new diarrheal episode, subtract 'Total days in all diarrheal episodes' from 'Total diarrheal surveillance days.' Diarrhea episodes were separated by two diarrhea-free days. Days when data were missing were classified as diarrhea-free (if there were two missing days before a day with diarrhea, the episode started on day with diarrhea). Days with Lactulose:Mannitol (L:M)-induced diarrhea were classified as diarrhea-free. Surveillance was conducted twice weekly for up to 3 years of age to assess illness on all days since the last surveillance visit.

label: Total diarrheal episodes
definition: Total number of distinct diarrheal episodes reported. Diarrhea episodes were separated by two diarrhea-free days. Days when data were missing were classified as diarrhea-free (if there were two missing days before a day with diarrhea, the episode started on day with diarrhea). Days with Lactulose:Mannitol (L:M)-induced diarrhea were classified as diarrhea-free. Surveillance was conducted twice weekly for up to 3 years of age to assess illness on all days since the last surveillance visit.

label: Cumulative diarrheal episode count
definition: Cumulative count of diarrheal episodes since beginning of follow-up. Diarrhea episodes were separated by two diarrhea-free days. Days when data are missing were classified as diarrhea-free (if there were two missing days before a day with diarrhea, the episode started on day with diarrhea). Days with Lactulose:Mannitol (L:M)-induced diarrhea were classified as diarrhea-free. Surveillance was conducted twice weekly for up to 3 years of age to assess illness on all days since the last surveillance visit.; Cumulative number of diarrheal episodes at each study visit.

label: Cumulative days within diarrheal episodes; Cumulative days with diarrhea
definition: Cumulative count of days that fall within any diarrheal episode since beginning of follow-up. Diarrhea episodes were separated by two diarrhea-free days. Days when data are missing were classified as diarrhea-free (if there were two missing days before a day with diarrhea, the episode started on day with diarrhea). Days with Lactulose:Mannitol (L:M)-induced diarrhea were classified as diarrhea-free. Surveillance was conducted twice weekly for up to 3 years of age to assess illness on all days since the last surveillance visit.

label: Days since last diarrheal episode
definition: Days since the last diarrheal episode ended (missing indicates time from birth until first episode). Diarrhea episodes were separated by two diarrhea-free days. Days when data are missing were classified as diarrhea-free (if there were two missing days before a day with diarrhea, the episode started on day with diarrhea). Days with Lactulose:Mannitol (L:M)-induced diarrhea were classified as diarrhea-free. Surveillance was conducted twice weekly for up to 3 years of age to assess illness on all days since the last surveillance visit.

label: Days between diarrheal episodes
definition: Days until the next diarrheal episode starts (missing indicates time from last episode to end of follow-up, or from birth if the participant never had diarrhea during the follow-up period). Days when data are missing were classified as diarrhea-free (if there were two missing days before a day with diarrhea, the episode started on day with diarrhea). Days with Lactulose:Mannitol (L:M)-induced diarrhea were classified as diarrhea-free. Surveillance was conducted twice weekly for up to 3 years of age to assess illness on all days since the last surveillance visit.

label: Study-defined ALRI
definition: Whether the participant had an acute lower respiratory Infection (ALRI). Participants who had a cough or shortness of breath (today or yesterday) PLUS a rapid respiratory rate (defined as: >60 breaths/min in participants aged 0 to <2 months, >50 breaths/min in participants aged 2 to <12 months and >40 breaths/min in participants aged 12 months to three years) were determined to have ALRI. Surveillance was conducted twice weekly for up to 3 years of age to assess illness on all days since the last surveillance visit.

label: ALRI episode status
definition: Whether this day of observation marked the beginning of a acute lower respiratory infection (ALRI) episode or was within an ALRI episode. ALRI episodes were separated by 14 ALRI-free days. Days when data are missing were classified as ALRI-free (if there were 14 missing days before a day with ALRI, the episode started on day with ALRI). Surveillance was conducted twice weekly for up to 3 years of age to assess illness on all days since the last surveillance visit.

label: ALRI episode #

Days when data are missing were classified as ALRI-free (if there were 14 missing days before a day with ALRI, the episode started on day with ALRI). Surveillance was conducted twice weekly for up to 3 years of age to assess illness on all days since the last surveillance visit.

definition: Whether a stool sample was collected from the participant during the surveillance visit. label: ALRI, fieldworker assessment
definition: Whether the field worker determined that the participant had an acute lower respiratory Infection (ALRI) during the surveillance visit. Participants who had a cough or shortness of breath PLUS rapid respiratory rate (defined as: >60 breaths/min in participants aged 0 to <2 months, >50 breaths/min in participants aged 2 to <12 months and >40 breaths/min in participants aged 12 months to three years) were determined to have ALRI and were referred to the nearest health center for assessment and treatment. Surveillance was conducted twice weekly for up to 3 years of age to assess illness on all days since the last surveillance visit.

label: Referral, fieldworker assessment
definition: Whether the field worker referred the participant for medical care during the surveillance visit. The participant was referred to the nearest health center for assessment and treatment if: (i) their temperature was above 39C; (ii) they passed 8 or more loose stools in a 24 hour period; (iii) had blood in their stool; (iv) had severe dehydration; or (v) if the field worker determined that the participant had an acute lower respiratory infection (ALRI). Whenever a participant produced at least 3 loose stools in a single day, diarrheal stool samples were collected before the end of the episode. Work up for detection of enteric pathogens was performed on the first stool sample collected during each diarrheal episode until 24 months of age (with a possible extension to 36 months of age).
variables: micro x::eaec cum d; eaec cum d
parent_label: Enteroaggregative Escherichia coli (EAEC) aggregate data; Enteroaggressive Escherichia coli (EAEC) aggregate data

label: Cumulative sum EAEC-pos 1st monthly stools

Work up for detection of enteric pathogens was performed on first monthly asymptomatic stool samples collected at 1-12, 15, 18, 21, and 24 months of age (with the option to test additional monthly stool samples to 36 months of age).

label: Monthly stool collection #
definition: The Nth stool collected in the sequence of asymptomatic monthly stool samples collected for a specific month, regardless of protocol. Occasionally, more than one non-diarrheal stool sample is collected in a specific month. Monthly asymptomatic stool samples were collected every month from 0-24 months of age, with a possible extension to 36 months of age.

label: Stool type, physiologic; Stool type, based on surveillance
definition: Type of stool type collected, using information from surveillance. 'Diarrhea stools' were samples with a liquid or watery consistency where diarrhea was reported within +/- 2 days of stool collection. 'Monthly stools' were collected more than 2 days away from an episode of study-defined diarrhea. Surveillance was conducted twice weekly for up to 3 years of age to assess illness on all days since the last surveillance visit. Whenever a participant produced at least 3 loose stools in a single day, diarrheal stool samples were collected before the end of the episode. Work up for detection of enteric pathogens was performed on diarrheal stool samples collected until 24 months of age (with a possible extension to 36 months of age) and on first monthly asymptomatic stool samples collected at 1-12, 15, 18, 21, and 24 months of age (with the option to test additional monthly stool samples to 36 months of age).

label: Per protocol diarrheal stool collection
definition: Whether this diarrheal stool sample was collected per the MAL-ED study protocol. Per protocol diarrheal stools included samples collected before the end of each diarrheal episode (whenever a participant produced at least 3 loose stools in a single day) as well as additional stool samples collected for a specific diarrhea episode after 14 study-defined diarrhea days in the same episode. Whenever a participant produced at least 3 loose stools in a single day, diarrheal stool samples were collected before the end of the episode. Diarrheal stool samples were collected until 36 months of age.

label: Cumulative per protocol diarrheal stool count; Cumulative per protocol diarrheal stool sample count

Whenever a participant produced at least 3 loose stools in a single day, diarrheal stool samples were collected before the end of the episode. Diarrheal stool samples were collected until 36 months of age.

definition: Whether the participant was fed the first milk (colostrum). Baseline breastfeeding information was collected upon enrollment.

label: Prelacteal feeding
definition: Whether there was prelacteal feeding of the participant. Baseline breastfeeding information was collected upon enrollment.

label: Cumulative days exclusively breastfed
definition: Cumulative sum of days with exclusive breastfeeding (ie, number of days, from birth to date, that the participant was reported to be exclusively breastfed). Between birth and the 1st bi-weekly breastfeeding survey, participants who began breastfeeding at all were considered to be exclusively breastfed. Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.; Assessed at each week of observation and prior to each diarrheal episode.
variables: bf2::cumexc; ext mgmt bv ddep st::epiexlbf; ext mgmt bv danth::vstexlbf; cumexc

label: Cumulative days not breastfed
definition: Cumulative sum of days with no breastfeeding (ie, number of days, from birth to date, that the participant was reported to not be breastfed). Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.

label: Cumulative days partially breastfed
definition: Cumulative sum of days with partial breastfeeding (ie, number of days, from birth to date, that the participant was reported to be partially breastfed). Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.

label: Cumulative days predominantly breastfed
definition: Cumulative sum of days with predominant breastfeeding (ie, number of days, from birth to date, that the participant was reported to be predominantly breastfed). Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.

label: Dairy reported at last visit
definition: Whether presence of dairy (milk, formula, yogurt, cheese, or other dairy products) in the diet was reported at the last breastfeeding surveillance visit. Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.

label: Exclusively breastfed at last visit; Exclusively breastfed
definition: Whether exclusive breastfeeding (breastfeeding present with no other liquids or solids) was reported at the last visit. Participants could switch back and forth between exclusive and different types of non-exclusive breastfeeding. Data between breastfeeding surveillance visits were filled in forward. Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.

label: Age at 1st day of biweekly breastfeeding surveillance (days)
definition: Minimum age in days at which bi-weekly breastfeeding surveillance data is available. Baseline breastfeeding information was collected upon enrollment.

label: Age 1st animal milk or formula given (days)
definition: Age in days at which first animal milk (including animal milk ingested with tea in Pakistan) or formula was given. This variable changed feeding definitions for 'Breastfeeding status' and 'Age last exclusively breastfed (days)' starting with the first occasion animal milk or formula were given, and did not allow for back and forth. Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.

label: Age at complete weaning (days)
definition: Age in days at which breastfeeding ceases (complete weaning), if observed at all. This variable changed feeding definitions for 'Breastfeeding status' and 'Age last exclusively breastfed (days)' starting with the first occasion complete weaning was observed, and did not allow for back and forth. Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.

label: Age 1st animal milk or solids given (days)
definition: Age in days at which first animal milk (including animal milk ingested with tea in Pakistan) OR solids was given. This variable changed feeding definitions for 'Breastfeeding status' and 'Age last exclusively breastfed (days)' starting with the first occasion animal milk or solids were given, and did not allow for back and forth. Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.

label: Age 1st clear liquid given (days)
definition: Age in days at which first clear liquid is given. This variable changed feeding definitions for 'Breastfeeding status' and 'Age last exclusively breastfed (days)' starting with the first occasion clear liquid was given, and did not allow for back and forth. Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.

label: Age 1st solid food given (days)
definition: Age in days at which first solid food is given. This variable changed feeding definitions for 'Breastfeeding status' and 'Age last exclusively breastfed (days)' starting with the first occasion solid food was given, and did not allow for back and forth. Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.

label: Not breastfed at last visit; Breastfeeding not reported last visit
definition: Whether no breastfeeding was reported at the last visit. Participants could switch back and forth between exclusive and different types of non-exclusive breastfeeding. Data between breastfeeding surveillance visits were filled in forward. Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.

label: Partially breastfed at last visit; Partially breastfed
definition: Whether partial breastfeeding (breastfeeding present with solids, animal milk (considering animal milk to be ingested with tea in Pakistan), and/or formula) was reported at the last visit. Participants could switch back and forth between exclusive and different types of non-exclusive breastfeeding. Data between breastfeeding surveillance visits were filled in forward. Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.

label: Predominantly breastfed at last visit; Predominantly breastfed
definition: Whether predominant breastfeeding (breastfeeding and clear liquids (water, fruit juice, tea, other liquids) present, with no solids, animal milk (considering animal milk to be ingested with tea in Pakistan), or formula) was reported at the last visit. Participants could switch back and forth between exclusive and different types of non-exclusive breastfeeding. Data between breastfeeding surveillance visits were filled in forward. Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.

label: Breastfeeding status
definition: Breastfeeding status was changed starting with the first occasion clear liquid, animal milk, formula, or solid food were given, and did not allow for back and forth. Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.

label: Age last exclusively breastfed (days)
definition: Maximum age in days of imputed exclusive breastfeeding (liquid or food given on next day), only including participants who were reported to be given non-breast milk foods. This variable changed starting with the first occasion clear liquid, animal milk, formula, or solid food were given, and did not allow for back and forth. Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.

label: Went 24hrs without food last month
definition: In the past four weeks, whether any member of the participant's household had go a whole day and night without eating anything because there was not enough food. Food security was assessed every 6 months from 0-24 months, with optional assessments at 30 and 36 months.

label: Ate foods not wanted last month
definition: In the past four weeks, whether any member of the participant's household had to eat some foods that they really did not want to eat because of a lack of resources to obtain other types of food. Food security was assessed every 6 months from 0-24 months, with optional assessments at 30 and 36 months.

label: Not able to eat preferred foods last month
definition: In the past four weeks, whether any member of the participant's household was not able to eat the kinds of foods they preferred because of a lack of resources. Food security was assessed every 6 months from 0-24 months, with optional assessments at 30 and 36 months.

label: Ate fewer meals due to lack of food last month
definition: In the past four weeks, whether any member of the participant's household had to eat fewer meals in a day because there was not enough food. Food security was assessed every 6 months from 0-24 months, with optional assessments at 30 and 36 months.

label: Went to sleep hungry last month
definition: In the past four weeks, whether any member of the participant's household had go to sleep at night hungry because there was not enough food. Food security was assessed every 6 months from 0-24 months, with optional assessments at 30 and 36 months.

label: Had to eat a limited variety of foods last month
definition: In the past four weeks, whether any member of the participant's household had to eat a limited variety of foods due to a lack of resources. Food security was assessed every 6 months from 0-24 months, with optional assessments at 30 and 36 months.

label: No food of any kind last month
definition: In the past four weeks, whether there was ever no food to eat of any kind in the participant's household because of lack of resources to get food. Food security was assessed every 6 months from 0-24 months, with optional assessments at 30 and 36 months. Note that for Brazil, the answer for this question is frequently '2 points - Sometimes,' instead of '0 points - No,' because the question was phrased as: 'In the past four weeks, whether some type of food of any kind was lacking in your household because of lack of resources to get food.'

label: Worried that there was not enough food last month
definition: In the past four weeks, whether the participant's mother, primary caregiver, or head of household worried that the household would not have enough food. Food security was assessed every 6 months from 0-24 months, with optional assessments at 30 and 36 months.

label: Ate smaller meal than needed last month
definition: In the past four weeks, whether any member of the participant's household had to eat a smaller meal than they felt they needed because there was not enough food. Food security was assessed every 6 months from 0-24 months, with optional assessments at 30 and 36 months.

label: Household Food Insecurity Access Scale (HFIAS)
definition: Category based on methods described in Coates et al. Household Food Insecurity Access Scale (HFIAS) for Measurement of Household Food Access: Indicator Guide (version 3). Food security was assessed every 6 months from 0-24 months, with optional assessments at 30 and 36 months.; Household Food Insecurity Access Scale category, based on method described in Coates et al. Household Food Insecurity Access Scale (HFIAS) for Measurement of Household Food Access: Indicator Guide (v. 3). Washington, DC: Food and Nutrition Technical Assistance Project, Academy for Educational Development, 2007.  Assessed for the household at enrollment (when target children were in utero).

label: Last contact date
definition: Date of last contact for participants lost to follow-up.

label: Age at last contact (days)
definition: Age (in days) of last contact for participants lost to follow-up.
variables: lmz::age lc; ext mgmt bv mib st::dropage; ldcdiff

label: Household Food Insecurity Access Scale (HFIAS) score
definition: Sum of 9 variables assessing household food security in the past four weeks. Values ranged from 0 (least insecure) to 27 (most insecure). Food security was assessed every 6 months from 0-24 months, with optional assessments at 30 and 36 months.; Sum of 9 variables assessing household food access in the past four weeks. Values can range from 0 (least food access insecure) to 27 (most food access insecure). Assessed for the household at enrollment (when target children were in utero).

label: Adjusted ferritin (ng/mL)
definition: Inflammation-adjusted concentration of ferritin in the blood (ng/mL), using site specific correction factors based on methods described in PMID: 16313694. Micronutrient status was assessed in blood samples collected at 7, 15, 24, and 36 months of age.

label: Adjusted retinol (ug/dL); Adjusted retinol (mg/dL)
definition: Inflammation-adjusted concentration of retinol in the blood (ug/dL), using site specific correction factors based on methods described in PMID: 16313694. Micronutrient status was assessed in blood samples collected at 7, 15, 24, and 36 months of age.

label: Soluble transferrin receptor (ug/mL); Soluble transferrin receptor (mg/L)
definition: Concentration of soluble transferrin receptor (TfR) in the blood (ug/mL). Micronutrient status was assessed in blood samples collected at 7, 15, 24, and 36 months of age.

label: Soluble transferrin receptor level
definition: Level of soluble transferrin receptor (TfR) in the blood. Micronutrient status was assessed in blood samples collected at 7, 15, 24, and 36 months of age.

label: Adjusted zinc (umol/L)
definition: Inflammation-adjusted concentration of zinc in the blood (umol/L), using site specific correction factors based on methods described in PMID: 16313694. All zinc data from South Africa has been excluded. Micronutrient status was assessed in blood samples collected at 7, 15, 24, and 36 months of age.

label: Anemia (hemoglobin less than 11g/dL)
definition: Whether the participant had anemia, defined as hemoglobin levels less than 11g/dL. Only assessed for participants who were 'Eligible for clinical survey' and gave 'Consent for lab testing' and had 'Hemoglobin (g/dL)' result recorded.; Altitude-adjusted hemoglobin is less than 11g/dL. Hemoglobin was assessed in blood samples collected at 7, 15, 24, and 36 months of age.
variables: anemia11; hh member 12m::anemia11; hh member 06m::anemia11; hh member 18m::anemia11; hh member 00m::anemia11; mn blood::anemia; anemia

label: Zinc (umol/L)
definition: Concentration of zinc in the blood (umol/L). All zinc data from South Africa has been excluded. Micronutrient status was assessed in blood samples collected at 7, 15, 24, and 36 months of age.

label: Adjusted hemoglobin (g/dL); Hemoglobin, adjusted for high altitude (g/dL)
definition: Hemoglobin (g/dL), adjusted for high altitude in participants from Nepal and Tanzania. Hemoglobin was assessed in blood samples collected at 7, 15, 24, and 36 months of age.

label: High alpha-1-acid glycoprotein (greater than 100mg/dL)
definition: Concentration of alpha-1-acid glycoprotein in plasma is greater than 100mg/dL. For analysis of environmental enteropathy, systemic inflammation was evaluated at 7, 15, and 24 months of age using alpha-1-acid glycoprotein concentration.

label: High lead (greater than 10ug/dL)
definition: Concentration of lead in the blood is greater than 10ug/dL. Lead was assessed in blood samples collected at 15, 24, and 36 months of age.

label: Iodine level; Urine iodine level
definition: Level of iodine in urine. Iodine was assessed in urine samples collected at 6, 15, 24, and 36 months of age.

label: Low adjusted ferritin (less than 12ng/mL)
definition: Inflammation-adjusted concentration of ferritin in the blood is less than 12ng/mL. Micronutrient status was assessed in blood samples collected at 7, 15, 24, and 36 months of age.

label: Low adjusted retinol (less than 20ug/dL); Low adjusted retinol (less than 20mg/dL)
definition: Inflammation-adjusted concentration of retinol in the blood is less than 20ug/dL. Micronutrient status was assessed in blood samples collected at 7, 15, 24, and 36 months of age.

label: Low adjusted zinc (less than 9.9 umol/L)
definition: Inflammation-adjusted concentration of zinc in the blood is less than 9.9umol/L. All zinc data from South Africa has been excluded. Micronutrient status was assessed in blood samples collected at 7, 15, 24, and 36 months of age.

label: Severe anemia (hemoglobin less than 7g/dL)
definition: Altitude-adjusted hemoglobin is less than 7g/dL. Hemoglobin was assessed in blood samples collected at 7, 15, 24, and 36 months of age.

label: Results from all gut inflammation tests available; Results from all 3 intestinal inflammation tests available
definition: Whether results from alpha-1-antitrypsin, myeloperoxidase, and neopterin gut inflammation biomarker tests are available for the stool sample. To be included in the gut function analysis set used in PMID: 28396264, results from all 3 biomarker tests must be available. Whenever a participant produced at least 3 loose stools in a single day, diarrheal stool samples were collected before the end of the episode. First monthly asymptomatic stool samples were collected every month from 0-24 months of age, with a possible extension to 36 months of age. First monthly asymptomatic stool samples collected at 1-12, 15, 18, 21, and 24 months of age were included in analyses of gut function.

label: Diarrheal stool; Diarrheal stool sample
definition: Whether this stool sample was considered a diarrheal stool by the MAL-ED Gut Function Technical Subcommittee. Stools that were collected on a day that falls within a diarrheal episode or where the last diarrheal episode ended less than or equal to 7 days ago met this definition. Whenever a participant produced at least 3 loose stools in a single day, diarrheal stool samples were collected before the end of the episode. First monthly asymptomatic stool samples were collected every month from 0-24 months of age, with a possible extension to 36 months of age.
variables: mpo neo ala::diarrhea gf; diarrhea gf

First monthly asymptomatic stool samples were collected every month from 0-24 months of age, with a possible extension to 36 months of age. First monthly asymptomatic stool samples collected at 1-12, 15, 18, 21, and 24 months of age were included in analyses of gut function.

label: L:M excretion test 1 day before stool collection; Lactulose-to-mannitol excretion test 1 day before stool collection

definition: Natural log of [myeloperoxidase (ng/mL) + 0.000001] concentration in the stool sample, a gut inflammation biomarker used for analysis of environmental enteropathy. label: Income score
definition: Average monthly income for the entire household, converted to US Dollars, categorized into all-site noniles. Used as a component in calculating the WAMI index. Values ranged from 0 (low) to 8 (high). Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months.

label: Drinking water score; Drinking water source categorization
definition: Whether the household drinking water source was categorized as improved or unimproved, based on WHO definitions. Drinking water sources categorized as 'Improved' include water that is 'Piped into dwelling' or 'Piped into yard or plot,' or from a 'Public tap or stand pipe;' a 'Tube well or borehole;' or a 'Protected well.' Drinking water sources categorized as 'Unimproved' include water that is from an 'Unprotected well' or 'Surface water.' Other sources of drinking water were considered 'Improved,' except for Peru where it was considered 'Unimproved' due to site-specific circumstances. Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months.

label: Mean people per room
definition: Mean number of persons per room used for sleeping.; Mean number of people sleeping in each room in the dwelling. Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months.

label: Maternal education (years)
definition: Years of schooling that the participant's mother had completed, beginning with kindergarten and through any university or post-university education. Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months.; Number of years of education completed by the target child participant's mother. Assessed for the household at enrollment (when target children were in utero).

label: Family income (USD)
definition: Average monthly income for the entire household, converted to US Dollars. Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months.

label: Sanitation score; Sanitation categorization
definition: Whether the household sanitation facilities were classified as improved or unimproved, based on WHO definitions. Sanitation facilities categorized as 'Improved' include those classified as 'Other,' 'Pit latrine without flush/with slab,''Flush to piped sewer system,' 'Flush to septic tank,' 'Flush to pit latrine,' or 'Flush to somewhere else.' 'No facility/bush/field or bucket toilet/pit latrine without slab' was considered 'Unimproved.' Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months.

label: Overall socioeconomic score
definition: Sum of all 4 components used to calculate the WAMI index: (i) 'Sanitation and drinking water score,' (ii) 'Assets score,' (iii) 'Income score,' and (iv) 'Maternal education score.' Values ranged from 0 (low) to 32 (high). Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months.

label: Fewer than 2 people per room; Mean people per room categorization
definition: Whether fewer than 2 people, on average, sleep in each room in the dwelling. Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months.

label: Toilet or latrine; Toilet
definition: Whether the household had a flush toilet or pit latrine. Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months.

label: Toilet or latrine has concrete floor
definition: Whether the household toilet or latrine had a concrete floor. Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months.

label: Toilet or latrine concrete floor before 11/2009
definition: For households with toilets or latrines that had a concrete floor, whether this concrete floor was available before November 2009. Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months.

label: Toilet or latrine concrete floor date
definition: Installation date for the household toilet or latrine's concrete floor, if after November 2009. Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months.

label: Toilet or latrine concrete floor between 11/2009-02/2014
definition: For households with toilets or latrines that did NOT have a concrete floor, whether the household toilet or latrine had a concrete floor at any time between November 2009 and February 2014. Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months.

label: Sanitation and drinking water score
definition: Sum of sanitation and drinking water scores. Used as a component in calculating the WAMI index. Households with 'Drinking water categorization' and 'Sanitation categorization' variables classified as 'improved' got a score of 4 for each; 'unimproved' responses got a score of 0 for each. Values ranged from 0 (low) to 8 (high). Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months.

label: WAMI index; WAMI
definition: An index of socio-economic status that includes access to improved water and sanitation, eight selected assets, maternal education, and household income. The WAMI index was calculated by dividing the 'Overall socioeconomic score' by 32. Values ranged from 0 (low) to 1 (high). Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months.

label: Animal proteins (meat, eggs, fish)
definition: Whether the participant consumed any animal proteins (including meat, egg, and fish) yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Diet diversity score for children 0 to 5 months
definition: Diet diversity score for children 0-5 months of age. Values ranged from 0-4. 4 was the highest diversity score a child could receive if he/she consumed breast milk and did not consume tea, milk, juices, formula, or solids in the previous day. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Diet diversity score for children 6 to 8 months
definition: Diet diversity score for children 6-8 months of age. Values ranged from 0-6. 6 was the highest diversity score a child could receive if he/she consumed breast milk and 4 or more food groups, fed at least 5 times, and did not consume formula in the previous day. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Animal proteins (meat, organ meat, fish)
definition: Whether the participant consumed any animal proteins (including meat, organ meat, and fish) yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Animal proteins (including grains and roots)
definition: Whether the participant consumed any animal proteins (including grains and roots) yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Complementary food introduction
definition: Whether participants 6-8 months of age had been introduced to complimentary foods (any solid, semi-solid,or soft foods) as of yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Dark green leafy vegetables, organ meat, any meat
definition: Whether the participant consumed any iron-rich or iron-fortified foods (including dark green leafy vegetables, organ meat and any meat) yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Organ meat, any meat
definition: Whether the participant consumed any iron-rich or iron-fortified foods (including organ meat and any meat) yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Dark green leafy vegetables, organ meat, any meat, eggs
definition: Whether the participant consumed any iron-rich or iron-fortified foods (including dark green leafy vegetables, organ meat, any meat, and eggs yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Organ meat, any meat, eggs
definition: Whether the participant consumed any iron-rich or iron-fortified foods (including organ meat, any meat, and eggs) yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Dark green leafy vegetables, organ meat, any meat, fish
definition: Whether the participant consumed any iron-rich or iron-fortified foods (including dark green leafy vegetables, organ meat, any meat, and fish) yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Organ meat, any meat, fish
definition: Whether the participant consumed any iron-rich or iron-fortified foods (including organ meat, any meat, and fish) yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Dark green leafy vegetables, organ meat, any meat, eggs, fish
definition: Whether the participant consumed any iron-rich or iron-fortified foods (including dark green leafy vegetables, organ meat, any meat, eggs and fish) yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Organ meat, any meat, eggs, fish
definition: Whether the participant consumed any iron-rich or iron-fortified foods (including organ meat, any meat, eggs and fish) yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Min acceptable diet for breastfed children
definition: Whether the minimum acceptable diet was met yesterday among breastfed children. Minimum acceptable diet for breastfed children was defined as breastfed children 6-23 months of age who had at least the minimum dietary diversity and the minimum meal frequency during the previous day. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Min acceptable diet for non-breastfed children
definition: Whether the minimum acceptable diet was met yesterday among non-breastfed children. Minimum acceptable diet for non-breastfed children was defined as non-breastfed children 6-23 months of age who received at least 2 milk feedings and had at least the minimum dietary diversity not including milk feeds and the minimum meal frequency during the previous day. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Min diet diversity of at least 4 food groups yesterday
definition: Minimum dietary diversity (consumption of 4 or more food groups) met during the previous day. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Animal milk or formula feedings yesterday
definition: Sum of animal milk and formula feeds yesterday, during night and day. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: More than 1 animal milk or formula feeds for non-breastfed kids
definition: Whether the sum of animal milk and formula feeds yesterday was greater than 1 for non breastfed kids. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: WHO min meal frequency met
definition: Whether the minimum meal frequency, based on the WHO core indicator definition (2 meals for breastfed children, 4 meals for non-breastfed children), was met yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Legumes
definition: Whether the participant consumed any foods made with beans, lentils, peas, corn, ground nuts yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Active breastfeeding
definition: Whether the participant actively breastfed yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Breastfeedings yesterday, daytime
definition: Number of times the participant was breastfed yesterday, from sunrise to sunset. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Breastfeedings yesterday, nighttime
definition: Number of times the participant was breastfed last night, from sunset to sunrise. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Commercially available foods
definition: Consumption of commercially available foods yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Dairy
definition: Whether the participant consumed any cheese, yogurt or other dairy products yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Eggs

label: Feedings yesterday

label: Fish or shellfish
definition: Whether the participant consumed any fresh or dried fish or shellfish yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Semi solid, mashed, or solid foods
definition: Whether the participant consumed any semi-solid, mashed or solid foods yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Formula feedings yesterday, daytime; Formula feedings yesterday
definition: Number of times the participant was fed formula yesterday, from sunrise to sunset. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Formula feedings yesterday, nighttime; Formula feedings last night
definition: Number of times the participant was fed formula last night, from sunset to sunrise. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Other fruits or vegetables
definition: Whether the participant consumed any other fruits or vegetables such as banana, apple, oranges, tomatoes, or avocados yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Grains
definition: Whether the participant consumed any rice, porridge, bread, noodles or other foods made from grains yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Fruit or vegetable juice
definition: Whether the participant consumed any fruit or vegetable juices yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Meat
definition: Whether the participant consumed any meat (chicken, beef, lamb, goat, duck, or others) yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Animal milk
definition: Whether the participant was given other milks (such as tinned, powdered or fresh animal milk) yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Animal milk feedings yesterday, daytime
definition: Number of times the participant was fed animal milk yesterday, from sunrise to sunset. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Animal milk feedings yesterday, nighttime
definition: Number of times the participant was fed animal milk last night, from sunset to sunrise. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Organ meats
definition: Whether the participant consumed any liver, kidney, heart or other organ meats yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Other liquids (soup, broth, sugar water, carbonated drinks)
definition: Whether the participant consumed any other liquids, such as sugar water, thin soup or broth, carbonated drinks, or local equivalents yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Roots or tubers
definition: Whether the participant consumed any white potatoes, white yams, manioc, or other foods made from roots yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Dark green leafy vegetables
definition: Whether the participant consumed any dark green leafy vegetables such as spinach yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Sweets
definition: Whether the participant consumed any sugary foods such as pastries, cakes or biscuits yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Coffee or tea
definition: Whether the participant consumed any tea, coffee, or local equivalents yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Plain water
definition: Whether the participant consumed any plain water yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.; Asked of controls, "What type of diet does your child normally take?

label: Yellow fruits
definition: Whether the participant consumed any ripe mangoes, papayas, or other sweet yellow/orange or red fruit yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Yellow vegetables
definition: Whether the participant consumed any carrots, squash, or sweet potatoes that are yellow or orange inside yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Vitamin A fruits or vegetables
definition: Whether the participant consumed any vitamin A vegetable or fruit food groups (includes yellow fruit, spinach, yellow vegetables) yesterday. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

label: Different food groups consumed
definition: Sum of food groups consumed yesterday, based on WHO diet diversity for all children. Values ranged from 0-7. The 7 foods groups used for tabulation of this indicator were: (a) grains, roots and tubers; (b) legumes and nuts; (c) dairy products (milk, yogurt, cheese); (d) flesh foods (meat, fish, poultry and liver/organ meats); (e) eggs; (f) vitamin-A rich fruits and vegetables; (g) other fruits and vegetables. Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.
variables: whocoreallsites::whodd whocore; number of who food groups; whodd whocore

label: Latrine type, current
definition: Type of pit latrine used by members of the household at the time of survey. Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months.

label: Latrine type, previous
definition: Type of pit latrine previously used, if the style of pit latrine used by members of the household at the time of survey was different than the type used when the participant was 0-2 years of age. Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months.

label: Toilet or latrine type; Facility type
definition: Type of toilet or latrine facility usually used by members of the household. Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months.

label: Stool type, gut function
definition: Stool type definition from the MAL-ED Gut Function Technical Subcommittee. 'Other stools' were samples where diarrhea was reported within the preceding 7 days and/or the lactulose:mannitol test was performed on the day of or day before stool collection. 'Asymptomatic stools' were stool samples that did not meet this definition of 'Other stools.' Only 'Asymptomatic stools' were included in the gut function analysis set used in PMID: 28396264. Surveillance was conducted twice weekly for up to 3 years of age to assess illness on all days since the last surveillance visit. Whenever a participant produced at least 3 loose stools in a single day, diarrheal stool samples were collected before the end of the episode. First monthly asymptomatic stool samples were collected every month from 0-24 months of age, with a possible extension to 36 months of age. First monthly asymptomatic stool samples collected at 1-12, 15, 18, 21, and 24 months of age were included in analyses of gut function.
variables: mpo neo ala::stooltype gf; stooltype gf

label: Stool used for environmental enteropathy analysis; 1st monthly stool, for fecal biomarker testing
definition: Indicator to select the gut function analysis set of stool samples used in PMID: 28396264. Whenever a participant produced at least 3 loose stools in a single day, diarrheal stool samples were collected before the end of the episode. First monthly asymptomatic stool samples were collected every month from 0-24 months of age, with a possible extension to 36 months of age. First monthly asymptomatic stool samples collected at 1-12, 15, 18, 21, and 24 months of age were included in analyses of gut function.

label: Per protocol stool collection
definition: Whether this was a per protocol stool collection, as defined by the MAL-ED Gut Function Technical Subcommittee. Per protocol first monthly asymptomatic stool samples were collected at 1-12, 15, 18, 21, and 24 months of age. Per protocol diarrhea stool samples were collected on a day that falls within a diarrheal episode or where the last diarrheal episode ended less than or equal to 7 days ago.
variables: mpo neo ala::protocol gf; protocol gf

definition: Qualitative dietary diversity was assessed on a monthly basis up to and including 8 months of age.

Work up for detection of enteric pathogens was performed on diarrheal stool samples collected until 24 months of age (with a possible extension to 36 months of age) and first monthly asymptomatic stool samples collected at 1-12, 15, 18, 21, and 24 months of age (with the option to test additional monthly stool samples to 36 months of age).

definition: Detection of the following bacteria in stool samples. label: Campylobacter, by bacteriology cleaned result

Whenever a participant produced at least 3 loose stools in a single day, diarrheal stool samples were collected before the end of the episode. Work up for detection of enteric pathogens was performed on the first stool sample collected during each diarrheal episode until 24 months of age (with a possible extension to 36 months of age) and on first monthly asymptomatic stool samples collected at 1-12, 15, 18, 21, and 24 months of age (with the option to test additional monthly stool samples to 36 months of age).

definition: Results of Norovirus Genogroup identification by RT-PCR for this stool sample. Whenever a participant produced at least 3 loose stools in a single day, diarrheal stool samples were collected before the end of the episode. Work up for detection of enteric pathogens was performed on the first stool sample collected during each diarrheal episode until 24 months of age (with a possible extension to 36 months of age) and on first monthly asymptomatic stool samples collected at 1-12, 15, 18, 21, and 24 months of age (with the option to test additional monthly stool samples to 36 months of age).

label: ETEC LT-pos or ST-pos, by PCR result
definition: Whether Enterotoxigenic Escherichia coli (ETEC), as defined by the presence of either heat-labile enterotoxin (LT) or heat-stable enterotoxin (ST), was detected by PCR for this stool sample. Whenever a participant produced at least 3 loose stools in a single day, diarrheal stool samples were collected before the end of the episode. Work up for detection of enteric pathogens was performed on the first stool sample collected during each diarrheal episode until 24 months of age (with a possible extension to 36 months of age) and on first monthly asymptomatic stool samples collected at 1-12, 15, 18, 21, and 24 months of age (with the option to test additional monthly stool samples to 36 months of age).

label: Rotavirus (post-vax corrected), by ELISA
definition: Whether Rotavirus was detected by ELISA for this stool sample. Any positive Rotavirus test result within 28 days of Rotavirus vaccination was changed to be a negative result. Whenever a participant produced at least 3 loose stools in a single day, diarrheal stool samples were collected before the end of the episode. Work up for detection of enteric pathogens was performed on the first stool sample collected during each diarrheal episode until 24 months of age (with a possible extension to 36 months of age) and on first monthly asymptomatic stool samples collected at 1-12, 15, 18, 21, and 24 months of age (with the option to test additional monthly stool samples to 36 months of age).

label: EAEC aatA-pos and aaiC-pos, by PCR result
definition: Whether Enteroaggregative Escherichia coli (EAEC), as defined by the presence of both aaiC and aatA (E. coli virulence genes), was detected by PCR for this stool sample. Whenever a participant produced at least 3 loose stools in a single day, diarrheal stool samples were collected before the end of the episode. Work up for detection of enteric pathogens was performed on the first stool sample collected during each diarrheal episode until 24 months of age (with a possible extension to 36 months of age) and on first monthly asymptomatic stool samples collected at 1-12, 15, 18, 21, and 24 months of age (with the option to test additional monthly stool samples to 36 months of age).

label: Target month for urine collection for iodine analysis
definition: Urine samples were collected at 3, 6, 9, 15, 24, and 36 months of age. Iodine was assessed in urine samples collected at 6, 15, 24, and 36 months of age.

label: Bacteria in nasopharyngeal/oropharyngeal swabs
definition: Common colonizers defined as CMV, H. influenzae, M. pneumoniae, Moraxella species, S. pneumoniae, and S. aureus. Klebsiella pneumoniae was considered a contaminant due to difficulties with assay specificity. For "absolute qPCR" variables, the sample was considered positive if above the qPCR density thresholds (see PERCH publications). H. influenzae - 5.9 log10 copies/mL, S. pneumoniae 6.9 log10 copies/mL.

label: Eukaryota in nasopharyngeal/oropharyngeal swabs
definition: Normalized defined as above the quantitative PCR density thresholds (see PERCH publications). P. jirovecii - 4.0 log10 copies/mL.

label: Virus in nasopharyngeal/oropharyngeal swabs
definition: Common colonizer defined as CMV. Measles testing was only performed on cases who met the clinical criteria for measles testing (history of measles in past month, measles rash, measles admission diagnosis, measles discharge diagnosis). "Absolute qPCR" variables were considered positive if above the qPCR density thresholds (see PERCH publications). CMV - 4.9 log10 copies/mL.

variables: o2 saturation fu v2; o2 saturation fu; oxygen; cfuplsox24;  o2sat; cfuplsox48

label: O2 saturation level
definition: Oxygen saturation was measured at admission, 24-hour follow-up, and 48-hour follow-up timepoints and only collected for cases. Cases with oxygen saturation measured while on oxygen are categorized with those who had an oxygen saturation 61-91%. Oxygen saturation categories are decreased by 2% for sites are higher altitude (Zambia and South Africa).

label: Oxygen source
definition: Source of oxygen at time of O2 saturation reading was measured at admission, 24-hour follow-up, and 48-hour follow-up timepoints and only collected for cases.

label: Oxygen support
definition: Oxygen support was measured at admission, 24-hour follow-up, and 48-hour follow-up timepoints and only collected for cases.

label: Severe or very severe pneumonia eligibility
definition: Severe pneumonia was defined as cough or difficulty breathing with lower chest wall indrawing. Very severe pneumonia was defined as cough or difficulty breathing and at least one of the following signs: central cyanosis, difficulty breastfeeding or drinking, vomiting everything, multiple or prolonged convulsions, lethargy or unconsciousness, or head nodding.

label: Difficulty breathing, caregiver report
definition: Based on parental recall. Collected for both cases and controls.

label: Lethargic
definition: If the child was lethargic at admission, including 1) responds to voice, 2) responds to pain, or 3) unresponsive. Only collected for cases.
parent_label: Severe or very severe pneumonia eligibility

label: Union council
definition: The smallest rural administrative or local government unit in Bangladesh.

label: Compound study arm
definition: The actual randomized, blinded intervention assigned to the compound. Compounds consisted of multiple households (typically 3 to 10 in Bangladesh), usually comprised of blood relatives, who share a common courtyard. Each randomization block was made up of 8 adjacent clusters (groups of 8 proximate compounds) that were pair-matched by geography. Each cluster within the randomization block was randomly allocated to one of 7 study arms, including 2 clusters randomly allocated to the control arm. A description of each study arm can be found on the study details page.

label: Compound study timepoint
definition: Survey data on compounds were collected at enrollment (year 0, baseline), 1 year post-intervention (midline), and 2 years post-intervention (endline). If you would like to view only data from a particular timepoint for all variables, please make sure to select that timepoint for variables in three locations: 'Compound study timepoint' (under 'Compound'), 'Household study timepoint' (under 'Household') and 'Study timepoint' (under 'Observation').

label: LNS consumed
definition: Number of lipid-based nutrient supplement (LNS) sachets consumed by the household per week. Based on counting sachets present at the time of a field visit. The expected number of sachets for 100% adherence is 14 sachets (7 days x 2 sachets per day). Values of LNS consumed that were negative or >28 were flagged.  Assessed for the household 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age).

label: LNS consumed flag
definition: Whether the number of lipid-based nutrient supplement (LNS) sachets consumed by the household per week was flagged for being negative or greater than 28. Assessed for the household 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age).

label: Percent LNS consumed
definition: Percent of expected lipid-based nutrient supplement (LNS) sachets consumed by the household per week. Based on counting sachets present at the time of a field visit. The expected number of sachets for 100% adherence is 14 sachets (7 days x 2 sachets per day). Values of LNS consumed that were negative or >28 were flagged. Assessed for the household 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age).

label: LNS consumed, caregiver report

The expected number of sachets for 100% adherence is 14 sachets (7 days x 2 sachets per day). Assessed for the household 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age).

label: Percent LNS consumed, caregiver report
definition: Percent of expected lipid-based nutrient supplement (LNS) sachets consumed by the household, as reported by the mother. The expected number of sachets for 100% adherence is 14 sachets (7 days x 2 sachets per day). Assessed for the household 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age). definition: Whether the target child participant's compound had a handwashing station with soap located within 6 steps of the kitchen. Assessed for the compound (multiple households sharing a common courtyard) at enrollment (when target children were in utero).

definition: Whether the target child participant was severely underweight, defined as having a weight-for-age z-score of less than -3. definition: Length- or height-for-age z-score for the target child participant, using median stature. Values greater than 6 or less than -6 were flagged and set to missing. label: Length- or height-for-age z-score flag
definition: Whether the length- or height-for-age z-score for the target child participant was flagged for being greater than 6 or less than -6. definition: Weight-for-length or -height z-score for the target child participant, using median weight and median length or height. definition: Whether the weight-for-length or -height z-score for the target child participant was flagged for being greater than 5 or less than -5. definition: Weight-for-age z-score for the target child participant, using median weight. Values greater than 5 or less than -6 were flagged and set to missing. label: Median stature (cm)
definition: Median stature of the target child participant, in cm. Stature was measured as either recumbent length or height while standing.  Anthropometry of target children was assessed 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age).

label: Stature (cm), 2nd
definition: Measurement #2 of the stature of the target child participant, in cm. Stature was measured as either recumbent length or height while standing. Anthropometry of target children was assessed 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age).

label: Stature (cm), 3rd
definition: Measurement #3 of the stature of the target child participant, in cm. Stature was measured as either recumbent length or height while standing. A 3rd measurement was only taken if the difference between measures 1 & 2 was greater than or equal to 0.5 cm. Anthropometry of target children was assessed 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age).

label: Median weight (kg)
definition: Median weight of the target child participant, in kg. Target child participant weight was either assessed directly or by measuring the weight of the mother plus the target child and subtracting out the mother's weight. Anthropometry of target children was assessed 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age).

label: Weight (kg), 2nd
definition: Direct measurement #2 of the weight of the target child participant, in kg. These direct weight measurement were reserved for endline anthropometric assessment and did not occur at the midline assessment. Target child participants who were not weighed directly at the endline assessment were weighed in combination with their mother.

label: Weight (kg), 3rd
definition: Direct measurement #3 of the weight of the target child participant, in kg. These direct weight measurement were reserved for endline anthropometric assessment and did not occur at the midline assessment. Target child participants who were not weighed directly at the endline assessment were weighed in combination with their mother. A 3rd measurement was only taken if the difference between measures 1 & 2 is greater than or equal to 0.1 kg.

label: Median head circumference (cm)
definition: Median head circumference of the target child participant, in cm. Anthropometry of target children was assessed 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age).

label: Head circumference (cm), 2nd
definition: Measurement #2 of the head circumference of the target child participant, in cm. Anthropometry of target children was assessed 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age).

label: Head circumference (cm), 3rd
definition: Measurement #3 of the head circumference of the target child participant, in cm. Anthropometry of target children was assessed 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age).

label: Caregiver plus participant weight (kg), 2nd
definition: Measurement #2 of the weight of the target child participant plus the mother, in kg. Anthropometry of target children was assessed 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age). Mother plus target child participant weights may not have been recorded at the endline anthropometry assessment if the target child was weighed directly.

label: Caregiver plus participant weight (kg), 3rd
definition: Measurement #3 of the weight of the target child participant plus the mother, in kg. A 3rd measurement was only taken if the difference between measures 1 & 2 is greater than or equal to 0.1 kg. Anthropometry of target children was assessed 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age). Mother plus target child participant weights may not have been recorded at the endline anthropometry assessment if the target child was weighed directly.

label: Caregiver weight (kg), 2nd
definition: Measurement #2 of the weight of the target child participant's mother, in kg. Anthropometry of target children was assessed 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age). Mother's weights may not have been recorded at the endline anthropometry assessment if the target child was weighed directly.

label: Caregiver weight (kg), 3rd
definition: Measurement #3 of the weight of the target child participant's mother, in kg. A 3rd measurement was only taken if the difference between measures 1 & 2 is greater than or equal to 0.1 kg. Anthropometry of target children was assessed 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age). Mother's weights may not have been recorded at the endline anthropometry assessment if the target child was weighed directly.

label: Chlorine detected in stored drinking water; Chlorine detected in compound's stored drinking water
definition: Whether more than 0.1 mg/L of free residual chlorine was detected in stored drinking water. Only water samples collected from compounds that reported treating their drinking water with some form of chlorine were tested. Assessed for the compound (multiple households sharing a common courtyard) 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age).

label: Compound stored drinking water
definition: Whether drinking water for the compound was stored. Assessed for the compound (multiple households sharing a common courtyard) at enrollment (when target children were in utero), 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age).

label: Field research assistant code
definition: Code to identify the field research assistant who took the measurement. This was used as an adjustment variable in case there was any measurement bias based on who collected the data.

label: Diarrhea case during the last 7 days, caregiver report
definition: Whether the participant was classified as a diarrhea case within the last 7 days. To meet the definition for a diarrhea case, the participant must have had 3+ loose or watery stools in 24 hours OR 1+ stool with blood. This variable, with a 7-day recall period, was used in the primary analysis to improve power as there was no evidence for differential recall by arm. Caregiver reported symptoms were assessed in target children 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age). Caregiver reported symptoms were also assessed in sibling/neighbor participants at enrollment, midline, and endline.

label: Diarrhea case during the last 2 days, caregiver report
definition: Whether the participant was classified as a diarrhea case within the last 2 days. To meet the definition for a diarrhea case, the participant must have had 3+ loose or watery stools in 24 hours OR 1+ stool with blood. Caregiver reported symptoms were assessed in target children 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age). Caregiver reported symptoms were also assessed in sibling/neighbor participants at enrollment, midline, and endline.

label: Loose or watery stools during last 7 days, caregiver report
definition: Whether the participant had loose or watery stools within in the last 2 days. Caregiver reported symptoms were assessed in target children 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age). Caregiver reported symptoms were also assessed in sibling/neighbor participants at enrollment, midline, and endline.

label: Loose or watery stools during last 2 days, caregiver report
definition: Whether the participant had loose or watery stools within in the last 2 days. Caregiver reported symptoms were assessed in target children 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age). Caregiver reported symptoms were also assessed in sibling/neighbor participants at enrollment, midline, and endline.

label: Blood in stool during last 7 days, caregiver report
definition: Whether the participant had blood in their stools within in the last 7 days. Caregiver reported symptoms were assessed in target children 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age). Caregiver reported symptoms were also assessed in sibling/neighbor participants at enrollment, midline, and endline.

label: Blood in stool during last 2 days, caregiver report
definition: Whether the participant had blood in their stools within in the last 2 days. Caregiver reported symptoms were assessed in target children 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age). Caregiver reported symptoms were also assessed in sibling/neighbor participants at enrollment, midline, and endline.

label: 3+ stools in 24hrs during last 7 days, caregiver report
definition: Whether the participant had 3 or more bowel movements in a 24 hour period within in the last 7 days. Caregiver reported symptoms were assessed in target children 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age). Caregiver reported symptoms were also assessed in sibling/neighbor participants at enrollment, midline, and endline.

label: 3+ stools in 24hrs during last 2 days, caregiver report

Caregiver reported symptoms were also assessed in sibling/neighbor participants at enrollment, midline, and endline.

Caregiver reported symptoms were also assessed in sibling/neighbor participants at enrollment, midline, and endline.

label: Phocine herpesvirus (positive control) Ct value, by TAC result
definition: Phocine herpes virus was spiked into every stool sample to control for extraction and amplification. Failure indicates that the sample was either inhibited, amplification failed, and/or extraction failed. For diarrheal stool samples, but not week 6 or week 10 stool samples, Ct values >= 35 are displayed as 35. Ct values of >= 35 are considered negative.
