label: Diphtheria toxoid IgG titer (IU/mL), by MIA result
definition: A multiplexed immuno assay was used. 0.01 IU/mL is protective. All values <0.001 IU/mL or below the standard curve were set to 0.001 IU/mL. Assessed at 53 weeks.

label: Filamentous hemagglutinin IgG titer (EU/mL), by MIA result
definition: A multiplexed immuno assay was used. Filamentous hemagglutinin (FHA) is included in pertussis vaccines. Values below 1 EU/mL or below the standard curve were set to 1 EU/mL. Assessed at 53 weeks.

label: Haemophilus influenzae type B IgG titer (ng/mL), by MIA result
definition: A multiplexed immuno assay was used. Values >1.0 ng/mL are considered protective. All values <0.01 ng/mL or below the standard curve were set to 0.01 ng/mL. Assessed at 53 weeks.

label: Measles IgG titer (IU/mL), by MIA result
definition: A multiplexed immuno assay was used. 0.12 IU/mL is protective. All values <0.001 IU/mL or below the standard curve were set to 0.001 IU/mL. Assessed at 53 weeks.

label: Pertactin IgG titer (EU/mL), by MIA result
definition: A multiplexed immuno assay was used. Pertactin (PRN) is included in pertussis vaccines. Values below 1 EU/mL or below the standard curve were set to 1 EU/mL. Assessed at 53 weeks.

label: Pertussis toxin IgG titer (EU/mL), by MIA result
definition: A multiplexed immuno assay was used. Values >62.5 EU/mL are indicative for infection in the past year. Values >125 EU/mL are indicitive for recent infection. Values below 1 EU/mL or below the standard curve were set to 1 EU/mL. Assessed at 53 weeks.

label: Tetanus toxoid IgG titer (IU/mL), by MIA result
definition: A multiplexed immuno assay was used. 0.01 IU/mL is protective. All values <0.001 IU/mL or below the standard curve were set to 0.001 IU/mL. Assessed at 53 weeks.

label: Polio vaccination dose per protocol
definition: Whether the participant received all intervention doses even if outside the visit window. The justification for relaxing the vaccination window requirement is partially based on the WHO recommendations which emphasize getting the required doses rather than exact ages for receiving the doses and the pragmatic concern of how far outside the window do we set the threshold.

label: Polio vaccination per protocol
definition: Whether strictly per protocol as described here. The participant (1) must have received all doses of vaccine as in protocol and according to assigned treatment arm, (2) receivedno extra vaccinations outside the protocol, (3) received all vaccinations as per vaccination window defined in the protocol, (4) should not have been terminated before the vaccination dose.

label: Received extra OPV
definition: Whether the participant received extra opv doses outside the study during the Bangladesh immunization campaign.

label: Polio serotype 1 seroconversion failure
definition: Seroconversion failure was derived based on the child's serum neutralizing antibodies (SNA) at 40 weeks (SNAwk40) and the maternal-antibody adjusted SNA at 18 weeks (SNAwk18). The participant was considered to have failed to seroconvert if a) SNAwk18  2.833 and SNAwk40  3 or b)  2.833< SNAwk18  8.5 and (SNAwk40 - SNAwk18) < 2 or c) 8.5 < SNAwk18 <10.5 and SNAwk40 < 10.5. Participants with SNAwk18   10.5 were excluded.

label: Polio serotype 2 seroconversion failure
definition: Seroconversion failure was derived based on the child's serum neutralizing antibodies (SNA) at 40 weeks (SNAwk40) and the maternal-antibody adjusted SNA at 18 weeks (SNAwk18). The participant was considered to have failed to seroconvert if a) SNAwk18  2.833 and SNAwk40  3 or b)  2.833< SNAwk18  8.5 and (SNAwk40 - SNAwk18) < 2 or c) 8.5 < SNAwk18 <10.5 and SNAwk40 < 10.5. Participants with SNAwk18   10.5 were excluded.

label: Polio serotype 3 seroconversion failure
definition: Seroconversion failure was derived based on the child's serum neutralizing antibodies (SNA) at 40 weeks (SNAwk40) and the maternal-antibody adjusted SNA at 18 weeks (SNAwk18). The participant was considered to have failed to seroconvert if a) SNAwk18  2.833 and SNAwk40  3 or b)  2.833< SNAwk18  8.5 and (SNAwk40 - SNAwk18) < 2 or c) 8.5 < SNAwk18 <10.5 and SNAwk40 < 10.5. Participants with SNAwk18   10.5 were excluded.

label: Cluster study arm, dichotomized
definition: Clusters were randomized to receive either conventional long-lasting insecticide-treated bednets (LLINs) or LLINs containing piperonyl butoxide (PBO). Conventional LLINs include PermaNet 2.0 and Olyset Net. PBO LLINs include PermaNet 3.0 and Olyset Plus.

label: Household study timepoint
definition: Cross-sectional surveys were conducted at baseline (month 0, prior to distribution of long-lasting insecticide-treated bednets (LLINs)) and at 6 months, 12 months, and 18 months after LLIN distribution. If you would like to view only data from a particular timepoint for all variables, please make sure to also select that timepoint for 'Household study timepoint' (under 'Household').; Survey data on households were collected at enrollment (year 0, baseline), 1 year post-intervention (midline), and 2 years post-intervention (endline).If you would like to view only data from a particular timepoint for all variables, please make sure to select that timepoint for variables in three locations: 'Compound study timepoint' (under 'Compound'), 'Household study timepoint' (under 'Household') and 'Study timepoint' (under 'Observation').

label: Enumeration area ID
definition: The primary sampling unit were  enumeration areas identified in the 2014 Ugandan national census. Ten enumeration areas were randomly selected in each of the health sub-districts. Within each sampled enumeration area, 5 households were randomly enrolled, for a total of 50 households sampled per cluster.

label: ITN bednet count categorization
definition: Categorization of the number of insecticide-treated bednets (ITNs) in the household.

label: Material burned
definition: If the household burned anything last night inside of the dwelling to keep mosquitoes away, specify what was burned. Only assessed for households included in the entomology survey.

label: Burn to keep mosquitoes away
definition: Whether the household burned anything last night inside of the dwelling to keep mosquitoes away. Only assessed for households included in the entomology survey.

label: Doors and windows closed
definition: Whether the doors and/or windows were closed last night to keep mosquitoes out of the house. Only assessed for households included in the entomology survey.

label: Insecticide last night
definition: Whether the household sprayed any insecticide inside of the dwelling last night. Only assessed for households included in the entomology survey.

label: Months since last IRS
definition: Number of months since indoor residual spraying (IRS) of interior walls of the dwelling against mosquitoes last occurred. Only assessed for households that were 'Sprayed in the last 12 months'.

label: Time doors and windows closed
definition: If the doors and/or windows were closed last night to keep mosquitoes out of the house, the time at which the doors and/or windows were closed. Only assessed for households included in the entomology survey.

label: Reason refused IRS
definition: Main reason the household did not grant permission for indoor residual spraying (IRS) of interior walls of the dwelling against mosquitoes. Only assessed for households that were not 'Sprayed in the last 12 months'.

label: 1 ITN per 2 people
definition: Whether there was at least 1 insecticide-treated bednet (ITN) per 2 people.

label: Household ITNs
definition: Whether the household has any insecticide-treated bednets (ITNs) that can be used while sleeping.

label: ITNs per person
definition: Number of insecticide-treated bednets (ITNs) per person in the household.

label: Relationship categorization
definition: Categorization of the relationship of the participant to the household head.
variables: hh member 18m::relationcat; hh member 06m::relationcat; hh member 00m::relationcat; hh member 12m::relationcat

label: Age <2 years
definition: Whether the participant was less than 2 years old.
variables: hh member 00m::lessthantwo; hh member 12m::lessthantwo; hh member 18m::lessthantwo; hh member 06m::lessthantwo

label: Internet device type
definition: The type of device that the household uses to access the internet.

label: Non-UCC bednets
definition: For households surveyed 12 or 18 months after the 2016-2017 Universal Coverage Campaign (UCC), whether there were any bednets in the household that were not received through the UCC. This question was skipped for households who did not receive a bednet through the UCC. This question was not asked at the 6 month study timepoint.

label: UCC LLIN received
definition: For households surveyed 6, 12, or 18 months after the 2016-2017 Universal Coverage Campaign (UCC), whether the household received one or more long-lasting insecticide-treated bednets (LLINs) during the UCC.

label: UCC LLIN instructions received
definition: For households surveyed 12 or 18 months after the 2016-2017 Universal Coverage Campaign (UCC), whether the household received any education on how to use or hang the long-lasting insecticide-treated bednets (LLINs) prior to or during the UCC. This question was skipped for households who did not receive a bednet through the UCC. This question was not asked at the 6 month study timepoint.

label: Remaining UCC LLIN count
definition: For households surveyed 12 or 18 months after the 2016-2017 Universal Coverage Campaign (UCC), the number of long-lasting insecticide-treated bednets (LLINs) received through the UCC that the household still had in their possession.  This question was skipped for households who did not receive a LLIN through the UCC. This question was not asked at the 6 month study timepoint.

label: Reason UCC LLIN not received
definition: For households surveyed 6, 12, or 18 months after the 2016-2017 Universal Coverage Campaign (UCC), the reason that the household did not receive a long-lasting insecticide treated bednet (LLIN) through the UCC.
variables: hh 18m::whynonet; hh 18m::whyother; hh 06m::whyother; hh 12m::whynonet; hh 12m::whyother; hh 06m::whynonet

label: UCC LLIN count
definition: For households surveyed 6, 12, or 18 months after the 2016-2017 Universal Coverage Campaign (UCC), the number of long-lasting insecticide-treated bednets (LLINs) the household received through the UCC. This question was skipped for households who did not receive a LLIN through the UCC.

label: UCC LLIN type
definition: For households surveyed 6, 12, or 18 months after the 2016-2017 Universal Coverage Campaign (UCC), the type of long-lasting insecticide-treated bednets (LLINs) the household received through the UCC. This question was skipped for households who did not receive a LLIN through the UCC.

label: Household head age, categorization (years)
definition: Categorization of the age (in years) of the head of the household.

label: Household head's sex
definition: The sex of the head of the household.

label: Intervention received
definition: Type of long-lasting insecticide-treated bednet (LLIN) actually received by the cluster, for per-protocol analysis. Certain clusters received a different LLIN type than that which was originally allocated to that cluster (the 'Intervention assignment'). Note that some clusters received a mix of LLIN types. For these clusters the dominant LLIN type was recorded for 'Intervention received'.

label: Intervention received, dichotomized
definition: Type of long-lasting insecticide-treated bednet (LLIN) actually received by the cluster, for per protocol analysis. Clusters received either conventional long-lasting insecticide-treated bednets (LLINs) or LLINs containing piperonyl butoxide (PBO). Conventional LLINs include PermaNet 2.0 and Olyset Net. PBO LLINs include PermaNet 3.0 and Olyset Plus.

label: Persons sleeping under bednet
definition: Total number of people who slept under a bednet in the house last night. Only assessed for households surveyed at baseline that were included in the entomology survey.

label: Persons sleeping under bednet, <5 years
definition: Number of people who slept under a bednet in the house last night who were younger than 5 years of age. Only assessed for households surveyed at baseline that were included in the entomology survey.

label: Persons sleeping under bednet, >15 years
definition: Number of people who slept under a bednet in the house last night who were older than 15 years of age. Only assessed for households surveyed at baseline that were included in the entomology survey.

label: Persons sleeping under bednet, 5 to 15 years
definition: Number of people who slept under a bednet in the house last night who were between 5 to 15 years of age. Only assessed for households surveyed at baseline that were included in the entomology survey.

label: Persons sleeping under bednet, other
definition: Number of people who slept under a bednet in the house last night who did not have an age recorded. Only assessed for households surveyed at baseline that were included in the entomology survey.

label: Crowding
definition: Whether there were 3 or more persons per room used for sleeping. Only assessed for households surveyed at baseline.

label: Persons in household, <5 years
definition: Whether any resident of the household was less than 5 years of age. Only assessed for households surveyed at baseline.

label: Persons sleeping in dwelling, <5 years
definition: Number of people who slept in the house last night who were younger than 5 years of age. Only assessed for households surveyed at baseline that were included in the entomology survey.

label: Persons sleeping in dwelling, >15 years
definition: Number of people who slept in the house last night who were older than 15 years of age. Only assessed for households surveyed at baseline that were included in the entomology survey.

label: Persons sleeping in dwelling, 5 to 15 years
definition: Number of people who slept in the house last night who were between 5 to 15 years of age. Only assessed for households surveyed at baseline that were included in the entomology survey.

label: Persons sleeping in dwelling, other
definition: Number of people who slept in the house last night who did not have an age recorded. Only assessed for households surveyed at baseline that were included in the entomology survey.

label: Months since last UCC LLIN distribution
definition: Number of months since the last time long-lasting insecticide-treated bednets (LLINs) were distributed by the Ministry of Health through a Universal Coverage Campaign (UCC). Only assessed for households surveyed at baseline, prior to the 2016-2017 UCC for LLIN distribution.

label: Months since last UCC LLIN distribution categorization
definition: Categorization of the number of months since the last time long-lasting insecticide-treated bednets (LLINs) were distributed by the Ministry of Health through a Universal Coverage Campaign (UCC). Only assessed for households surveyed at baseline, prior to the 2016-2017 UCC for LLIN distribution.

label: UCC LLIN wave
definition: Wave of long-lasting insecticide-treated bednet (LLIN) distribution during the 2016-2017 Universal Coverage Campaign (UCC). LLINs were distributed across Uganda in groups of districts at a time, and the LLIN distribution schedule was divided into waves. The LLINEUP study took place in districts that received LLINs during waves 2, 3, and 4.

label: Cluster-level mean female Anopheles
definition: Average number of female Anopheline mosquitoes in each household, per cluster. Calculated for baseline data only.

label: Cluster-level parasite prevalence categorization
definition: Categorization of Plasmodium parasite prevalence in each cluster. Calculated for baseline data only.

label: Log10 cluster-level anemia prevalence (<11g/dL)
definition: Log10 of the prevalence of anemia (defined as hemoglobin levels less than 11g/dL) in each cluster. Calculated for baseline data only.

label: Log10 cluster-level mean female Anopheles
definition: Log10 of the average number of female Anopheline mosquitoes in each household, per cluster. Calculated for baseline data only.

label: Log10 cluster-level parasite prevalence
definition: Log10 of the Plasmodium parasite prevalence in each cluster. Calculated for baseline data only.

label: Dehydration, caregiver report
definition: Participant's dehydration level, as reported by the mother. No dehydration was defined as: non-sunken eyes, no lethargy, easily consoled if irritable, drinks or breastfeeds well, normal abdominal skin pinch. Some dehydration was defined as: irritable/difficult to console, delay in skin pinch return, eyes sunken, when offered liquid drinks eagerly/demonstrates greater than normal thirst. Severe dehydration was defined as: lethargy, sunken eyes, listless, difficulty in mother/child interaction. If the mother reported severe dehydration, the participant was referred to the nearest health center for assessment and treatment. Surveillance was conducted twice weekly for up to 3 years of age to assess illness on all days since the last surveillance visit.
